  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a two-part quarto volume containing Job Baster's *Natuurkundige Uitspanningen, behelzende eenige waarneemingen over sommige zee-planten en zee-insecten, benevens derzelver zaadhuisjes en eyernesten* (\"Natural Recreations, containing some observations on certain sea-plants and sea-insects, together with their seed-vessels and egg-nests\"). Published by J. Bosch in Haarlem between 1759 and 1765, the work comprises Part I (169 pp, 16 plates) and Part II (167 pp, 13 plates), bound together as one volume. The 29 plates are hand-colored copperplate engravings depicting marine organisms — hydropolyps, corallines, mollusks, their eggs, and larvae. This is a foundational work in Dutch marine biology and one of the earliest systematic illustrated studies of invertebrate marine life from the North Sea and Oosterschelde.",
